The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           IN THE CITY
                  
	 Several athletes from Bengal have been selected for the National camps to be held in preparation for the 2010 Commonwealth Games. Sushmita Singha Roy and Abhishek Roy will be headed for the camp at SAI, Calcutta while Arjina Khatun has been selected for the camp at Thiruvanantapuram.          
	 A two-day seminar for East Zone Umpires under the aegis of the BCCI will be held at the Eden Gardens on Friday and Saturday.           
	 Bengal Motor Sports Club will hold its flagship event the Kaviguru Rally 2008 on August 30. The Kaviguru Rally for four and two wheelers will run from Calcutta to Shantiniketan covering approximately 300kms of rally track.                
	FOOTBALL: CFL Premier Division  East Bengal vs Mohun Bagan at Salt Lake Stadium from 4pm                                                                                                                                                                     
